claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: A table listing influenza vaccine products with columns for trade name (manufacturer), presentation, age indication, HA antigen content per dose, route, and mercury content. It includes standard-dose inactivated vaccines (15 µg/0.5 mL) and Flublok Quadrivalent (recombinant HA vaccine) at 45 µg/0.5 mL. Evidence: Flublok Quadrivalent contains 45 µg HA per 0.5 mL dose versus 15 µg/0.5 mL in standard-dose IIV4 vaccines. does not support the claim because while it shows Flublok has 3x the HA antigen content, it does not provide any evidence linking this increased content to greater immunogenicity versus standard-dose flu vaccines.
